SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 35-5-101, is amended by deleting the
section and substituting:
(a) In any sale of land to foreclose a deed of trust, mortgage, or other lien
securing the payment of money or other thing of value or under judicial orders or
process, advertisement of the sale must be made:
(1)
(A) For sales occurring prior to July 1, 2027, at least two (2) times
in a newspaper published in the county where the sale is to be made; or
(B) For sales occurring on or after July 1, 2027, at least one (1)
time in a newspaper published in the county where the sale is to be
made; and
(2) By a posting online by a third-party internet posting company for at
least twenty (20) continuous days. A posting made pursuant to this subdivision
(a)(2) must be posted online in a manner such that the posting is publicly
viewable to general internet users.
(b) The initial publication in a newspaper must be at least twenty (20) days
previous to the sale.
(c) This section does not apply:
(1) Where the amount of indebtedness for the payment of which the
property being sold does not amount to more than two hundred dollars ($200), in
